<h3 class="fw-bold">What is Basecamp?</h3>
<p>Basecamp is a web-based project management tool launched in 2004. It is widely used by teams to streamline their workflows through features like:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>To-do lists</strong> for task management</li>
  <li><strong>Milestone tracking</strong> to set project goals</li>
  <li><strong>Forum-style messaging</strong> for discussions</li>
</ul>

<h3 class="fw-bold">Why MyBasecamp1?</h3>
<p>MyBasecamp1 brings the essence of Basecamp into a <strong>modern, easy-to-use web application</strong>. Our platform allows users to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>✅ <strong>Sign up & manage accounts</strong></li>
  <li>✅ <strong>Log in & log out securely</strong></li>
  <li>✅ <strong>Create and manage projects</strong></li>
  <li>✅ <strong>Assign admin roles for better control</strong></li>
</ul>

<h3 class="fw-bold">Project Roadmap</h3>
<p>MyBasecamp1 is built in three phases, ensuring a smooth development process:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Phase 1:</strong> User Authentication – Register, log in, and manage user roles.</li>
  <li><strong>Phase 2:</strong> Project Management – Create, edit, and delete projects.</li>
  <li><strong>Phase 3:</strong> Enhanced Collaboration – Add messaging, task assignments, and more.</li>
</ul>
